riant), confirming no false-positive PR detection.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When a PR-create trigger is detected, the hook can reconstruct and persist the PR identifier needed by the review loop state.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: 'Persist' means writing to the filesystem; the failure mode involves both the extraction logic (parsing PR identifier from the command or its output) and the file-write path working together. Isolation to a single function would not exercise the path from detection → extraction → write. REAL-INFRA: Filesystem write is required, but a real temp directory (e.g., `tmp_path`) is sufficient — no network or subprocess needed. An in-process fake temp dir reproduces the exact failure. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the write call would confirm the call was made but not that the file is written with the correct content and structure. LLM-DEP: None. MULTI-STEP: None. Rejection of System: the write target is a local state file, not a real external service or subprocess.","test_description":"Invoke the hook's post-detection persistence function with a sample PR-create command string and a temp directory as the state root. Assert that a state file exists in the expected location and that its contents include the reconstructed PR identifier (e.g., PR number or URL extracted from the command arguments or stdout stub).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"After PR-create detection, the review gate state is written in a form that the pre-tool enforcement hook can read and enforce.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure boundary here is the contract between two separate hooks — the PostToolUse writer and the PreTool enforcement reader. Testing either hook in isolation cannot catch a format mismatch. The failure only appears when the reader's deserialization is exercised against real bytes written by the writer. REAL-INFRA: Both hooks operate on local files; a shared temp directory is sufficient. No real network or subprocess needed. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the reader would guarantee it accepts whatever the writer produces, hiding any schema/format drift. LLM-DEP: None. MULTI-STEP: The two hooks run in sequence, but both are deterministic code — no LLM step. Rejection of Workflow: no agentic steps are involved; this is two deterministic code modules exchanging a file. Rejection of System: a shared in-process temp directory reproduces the exact cross-hook failure.","test_description":"Run the PostToolUse hook's state-write path with a PR-create trigger input, writing into a shared temp directory. Then run the PreTool enforcement hook's state-read path pointing at the same temp directory. Assert the pre-tool hook correctly identifies the gate as active (i.e., a PR review is pending) and would block or flag further tool calls as required — verifying the full round-trip contract between the two hooks.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9819,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9819},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ff513b50-a0ca-49d9-8b2d-20528f696141","uuid":"16be8bf3-9c88-417f-9cd8-2ea94028da96"}
